  "texts": [
    "The United States is ranked third with 67 publications (10.36%) while Morocco and the United Kingdom are tied for fourth with 22 publications (3.4% each).",
    "In the subsequent years, eleven countries produced between 10 and 19 documents, while ten countries published between 5 and 9 documents.",
    "In addition, 17 countries have contributed between 2 and 4 documents, while 20 have published a single document.",
    "Adding the contributions from each country yields a total of 642 publications, which is greater than 524.",
    "This indicates that there has been an abundance of international collaboration.Table 3 provides statistics for a selection of the top 46 countries."
  ]
}